  "prompt": "What are the pros and cons of using Google Docs instead of a wiki for research projects' documentation?",
  "response": "Here are some pros and cons of using Google Docs versus a wiki for research project documentation:\n\nPros of Google Docs:\n- Easy to use and familiar interface\n- Excellent real-time collaboration features\n- Good version history tracking\n- Simple sharing and permissions\n- Works well with other Google tools\n- Can be easily exported to different formats\n- Free and widely accessible\n\nCons of Google Docs:\n- Less structured than a wiki\n- More difficult to organize large amounts of information\n- Limited hyperlinking capabilities\n- Less granular permissions\n- Not as good for creating interconnected knowledge bases\n- Less specialized for documentation\n\nPros of Wikis:\n- Better for creating linked, structured knowledge\n- More robust organization of information\n- Advanced linking and cross-referencing\n- Often have built-in categories and tagging\n- More flexible for complex documentation\n- Better for long-term knowledge management\n\nCons of Wikis:\n- Steeper learning curve\n- Often require more technical setup\n- Can be less intuitive for casual users\n- May have fewer collaboration features\n- Some require hosting and maintenance\n- Often less visually appealing\n\nThe best choice depends on your specific project needs, team technical skills, and documentation complexity.",
